CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 22, 1941, pg. 8 reads: "Artists Congratulated After Concert - The annual concert of The Urban League Choir at Foster Memorial Hall last Thursday evening was a musical triumph.  Here are pictured the artists after the performance...Right photo: Easton Keys, baritone, soloist and choir member, Miss Walls and Mr. Walls. - Harris photos."
TitMainTitle: Easton Keys, Mary Walls, and Raymond E. Walls standing in Foster Memorial Hall for annual concert of the Urban League Choir
